<!--  
     Schema for the Sales Analysis EC Sales Query Business Object
-->
<xsd:schema elementFormDefault="qualified" attributeFormDefault="unqualified" xmlns:xsd="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema">
  <xsd:element name="Filter">
    <xsd:complexType>
      <xsd:sequence>
        <xsd:element ref="InvoiceDate" minOccurs="0"/>
        <xsd:element ref="TariffCode" minOccurs="0"/>
      </xsd:sequence>
    </xsd:complexType>
  </xsd:element>
  <xsd:element name="ServiceEntries">
    <xsd:annotation>
      <xsd:documentation>This option is only available when running the Aggregate report. Valid values are 'I - Include (default), 'E' - Exclude and 'O' - Only.</xsd:documentation>
      <xsd:appinfo source="screenItem=Y;I=Include;E=Exclude;O=Only"/>
    </xsd:annotation>
    <xsd:simpleType>
      <xsd:restriction base="xsd:string">
        <xsd:minLength value="0"/>
        <xsd:maxLength value="1"/>
        <xsd:whiteSpace value="preserve"/>
        <xsd:enumeration value="I"/>
        <xsd:enumeration value="E"/>
        <xsd:enumeration value="O"/>
      </xsd:restriction>
    </xsd:simpleType>
  </xsd:element>
  <xsd:element name="InvoiceDate">
    <xsd:annotation>
      <xsd:documentation>The Sales Analysis EC Vat Sales file stores the date of each transaction.

This date is used to selectively print invoices as follows:

All 
Select this to include sales for all invoice dates.

Range 
Select this to include sales for a range of invoice dates.

You indicate this range in the From and To fields below.

Single 
Select this if you want to generate the report for sales for a single invoice date.

You indicate this invoice date in the From field below.

From 
This indicates the first invoice date in a range of invoice dates for which you want to include sales in the report.

If you selected to include sales for a single invoice date, then you enter that invoice date in this field.

To 
This indicates the last invoice date in a range of invoice dates for which you want to include sales in the report.


</xsd:documentation>
      <xsd:appinfo source="screenItem=Y;browse={date};A=All;S=Single;R=Range"/>
    </xsd:annotation>
    <xsd:complexType>
      <xsd:attribute name="FilterType" use="optional" default="A">
        <xsd:simpleType>
          <xsd:restriction base="xsd:string">
            <xsd:enumeration value="A"/>
            <xsd:enumeration value="S"/>
            <xsd:enumeration value="R"/>
          </xsd:restriction>
        </xsd:simpleType>
      </xsd:attribute>
      <xsd:attribute name="FilterValue" type="xsd:string" use="optional"/>
    </xsd:complexType>
  </xsd:element>
  <xsd:element name="MonthEndPeriod">
    <xsd:annotation>
      <xsd:documentation>The period end date defaults to the Accounts Receivable period end date (Accounts Receivable Setup - Current Month tab), but can be changed.

You use this option to indicate the month up to which you want to generate the report.

This option is ignored when you select to reprint the report. 

Month 
This indicates the month (within the year selected below), up to which to print the report
</xsd:documentation>
      <xsd:appinfo source="screenItem=Y;01=01;02=02;03=03;04=04;05=05;06=06;07=07;08=08;09=09;10=10;11=11;12=12"/>
    </xsd:annotation>
    <xsd:simpleType>
      <xsd:restriction base="xsd:string">
        <xsd:minLength value="0"/>
        <xsd:maxLength value="2"/>
        <xsd:whiteSpace value="preserve"/>
        <xsd:enumeration value="01"/>
        <xsd:enumeration value="02"/>
        <xsd:enumeration value="03"/>
        <xsd:enumeration value="04"/>
        <xsd:enumeration value="05"/>
        <xsd:enumeration value="06"/>
        <xsd:enumeration value="07"/>
        <xsd:enumeration value="08"/>
        <xsd:enumeration value="09"/>
        <xsd:enumeration value="10"/>
        <xsd:enumeration value="11"/>
        <xsd:enumeration value="12"/>
      </xsd:restriction>
    </xsd:simpleType>
  </xsd:element>
  <xsd:element name="Option">
    <xsd:complexType>
      <xsd:sequence>
        <xsd:element ref="ReportSelection" minOccurs="0"/>
        <xsd:element ref="ReportType" minOccurs="0"/>
        <xsd:element ref="MonthEndPeriod" minOccurs="0"/>
        <xsd:element ref="YearEndPeriod" minOccurs="0"/>
        <xsd:element ref="Reprint" minOccurs="0"/>
        <xsd:element ref="ReprintSinglePeriod" minOccurs="0"/>
        <xsd:element ref="ReprintPeriodMonth" minOccurs="0"/>
        <xsd:element ref="ReprintPeriodYear" minOccurs="0"/>
        <xsd:element ref="ServiceEntries" minOccurs="0"/>
      </xsd:sequence>
    </xsd:complexType>
  </xsd:element>
  <xsd:element name="Query">
    <xsd:complexType>
      <xsd:sequence>
        <xsd:element ref="Option"/>
        <xsd:element ref="Filter"/>
      </xsd:sequence>
    </xsd:complexType>
  </xsd:element>
  <xsd:element name="ReportSelection" default="A">
    <xsd:annotation>
      <xsd:documentation>Valid values are 'A' - Aggregate Listing (default) or 'S' - Suplementary Declaration report.

Aggregate sales listing 
Select this to print a report listing all sales made to EC countries.

This report uses data from the S/A EC VAT sales file to create the listing. Each invoiced line on a sales order for a customer in an EC Member State (excluding local transactions) creates an entry in this file.

This report only prints transactions for those EC customers for whom a VAT registration number is defined (Customers - Tax tab).

Supplementary declaration report 
Select this to print a report listing all despatches (goods issued from stock) to EC countries.

This report uses data from the S/A EC VAT sales file to create the listing. Each invoiced line on a sales order for a customer in an EC Member State (excluding local transactions) creates an entry in this file.
</xsd:documentation>
      <xsd:appinfo source="screenItem=Y;A=Aggregate Sales Listing;S=Supplemetary Declaration Report"/>
    </xsd:annotation>
    <xsd:simpleType>
      <xsd:restriction base="xsd:string">
        <xsd:minLength value="0"/>
        <xsd:maxLength value="1"/>
        <xsd:whiteSpace value="preserve"/>
        <xsd:enumeration value="S"/>
        <xsd:enumeration value="A"/>
      </xsd:restriction>
    </xsd:simpleType>
  </xsd:element>
  <xsd:element name="ReportType" default="S">
    <xsd:annotation>
      <xsd:documentation>Valid values are 'S' - Summary (default) or 'D' - Detail.

Summary 
Select this to exclude detail information from being printed on the report.

The aggregate sales listing report, lists the total sales value by customer tax registration number.

The supplementary declaration report, lists the total goods issued from stock by tariff code.

Detail 
Select this to print the detail information as well as totals on the report.

The aggregate sales listing report, lists all sales to each customer by document (invoice) number.

The supplementary declaration report, lists all goods issued from stock by invoice and sales order number.
</xsd:documentation>
      <xsd:appinfo source="screenItem=Y;S=Summary;D=Detail"/>
    </xsd:annotation>
    <xsd:simpleType>
      <xsd:restriction base="xsd:string">
        <xsd:minLength value="0"/>
        <xsd:maxLength value="1"/>
        <xsd:whiteSpace value="preserve"/>
        <xsd:enumeration value="S"/>
        <xsd:enumeration value="D"/>
      </xsd:restriction>
    </xsd:simpleType>
  </xsd:element>
  <xsd:element name="Reprint" default="N">
    <xsd:annotation>
      <xsd:documentation>Valid values are 'N' - No (default) or 'Y' - Yes.

Select this to print a report that was previously printed.</xsd:documentation>
      <xsd:appinfo source="screenItem=Y;Y=Yes;N=No"/>
    </xsd:annotation>
    <xsd:simpleType>
      <xsd:restriction base="xsd:string">
        <xsd:minLength value="0"/>
        <xsd:maxLength value="1"/>
        <xsd:whiteSpace value="preserve"/>
        <xsd:enumeration value="N"/>
        <xsd:enumeration value="Y"/>
      </xsd:restriction>
    </xsd:simpleType>
  </xsd:element>
  <xsd:element name="ReprintPeriodMonth">
    <xsd:annotation>
      <xsd:documentation>This indicates the month (within the year selected in 'ReprintPeriodYear'), for which you want to reprint the report.
</xsd:documentation>
      <xsd:appinfo source="screenItem=Y;01=01;02=02;03=03;04=04;05=05;06=06;07=07;08=08;09=09;10=10;11=11;12=12"/>
    </xsd:annotation>
    <xsd:simpleType>
      <xsd:restriction base="xsd:string">
        <xsd:minLength value="0"/>
        <xsd:maxLength value="2"/>
        <xsd:whiteSpace value="preserve"/>
        <xsd:enumeration value="01"/>
        <xsd:enumeration value="02"/>
        <xsd:enumeration value="03"/>
        <xsd:enumeration value="04"/>
        <xsd:enumeration value="05"/>
        <xsd:enumeration value="06"/>
        <xsd:enumeration value="07"/>
        <xsd:enumeration value="08"/>
        <xsd:enumeration value="09"/>
        <xsd:enumeration value="10"/>
        <xsd:enumeration value="11"/>
        <xsd:enumeration value="12"/>
      </xsd:restriction>
    </xsd:simpleType>
  </xsd:element>
  <xsd:element name="ReprintPeriodYear" default="C">
    <xsd:annotation>
      <xsd:documentation>This indicates the year for which the report must be printed.
Valida values are 'C' - Current (default), 'P' - Previous or a 4-digit field indicating the current or previous AR financial year.</xsd:documentation>
      <xsd:appinfo source="screenItem=Y;C=Current year;P=Previous year"/>
    </xsd:annotation>
    <xsd:simpleType>
      <xsd:restriction base="xsd:string">
        <xsd:minLength value="0"/>
        <xsd:maxLength value="1"/>
        <xsd:whiteSpace value="preserve"/>
        <xsd:enumeration value="C"/>
        <xsd:enumeration value="P"/>
      </xsd:restriction>
    </xsd:simpleType>
  </xsd:element>
  <xsd:element name="ReprintSinglePeriod" default="N">
    <xsd:annotation>
      <xsd:documentation>Valid values are 'N' - No (default) or 'Y' - Yes.
If you selected the Reprint option, then you will be able to select to print a single period or all periods.
Select 'N' reprint all the available data, regardless of the month and year.
Select a single period in elements 'ReprintPeriodMonth' and 'ReprintPeriodYear' to reprint all the available data, for one particular period only.</xsd:documentation>
      <xsd:appinfo source="screenItem=Y;Y=Yes;N=No"/>
    </xsd:annotation>
    <xsd:simpleType>
      <xsd:restriction base="xsd:string">
        <xsd:minLength value="0"/>
        <xsd:maxLength value="1"/>
        <xsd:whiteSpace value="preserve"/>
        <xsd:enumeration value="N"/>
        <xsd:enumeration value="Y"/>
      </xsd:restriction>
    </xsd:simpleType>
  </xsd:element>
  <xsd:element name="TariffCode">
    <xsd:annotation>
      <xsd:documentation>Range of tariff codes to be reported on. Valid values are 'A' - All (default), 'R' - Range or 'S' - Single.</xsd:documentation>
      <xsd:appinfo source="screenItem=Y;browse=LctTariff;A=All;S=Single;R=Range"/>
    </xsd:annotation>
    <xsd:complexType>
      <xsd:attribute name="FilterType" use="optional" default="A">
        <xsd:simpleType>
          <xsd:restriction base="xsd:string">
            <xsd:enumeration value="A"/>
            <xsd:enumeration value="R"/>
            <xsd:enumeration value="S"/>
          </xsd:restriction>
        </xsd:simpleType>
      </xsd:attribute>
      <xsd:attribute name="FilterValue" type="xsd:string" use="optional"/>
    </xsd:complexType>
  </xsd:element>
  <xsd:element name="YearEndPeriod" default="C">
    <xsd:annotation>
      <xsd:documentation>This indicates the year for which the report must be printed.
Valida values are 'C' - Current (default), 'P' - Previous or a 4-digit field indicating the current or previous AR financial year.</xsd:documentation>
      <xsd:appinfo source="screenItem=Y;C=Current year;P=Previous year"/>
    </xsd:annotation>
    <xsd:simpleType>
      <xsd:restriction base="xsd:string">
        <xsd:minLength value="0"/>
        <xsd:maxLength value="1"/>
        <xsd:whiteSpace value="preserve"/>
      </xsd:restriction>
    </xsd:simpleType>
  </xsd:element>
</xsd:schema>
